    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
      This project was developed for my <strong>Maths for Games</strong> module in second year.
      The goal was to apply mathematical concepts directly to gameplay systems — including
      vector operations, quaternions, projectile motion, and spline-based camera movement.
      It acted as both a technical learning exercise and a chance to build reusable math
      libraries for my later projects.
    </p>

